Differential Expression Analysis Using DESeq2

# Create DESeq2 object
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = assaydata,
                              colData = coldf,
                              design = ~ gender) # Designing gender since analysis will do with female vs male
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): 1233 duplicate
## rownames were renamed by adding numbers
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
levels(dds$gender)  # Look the levels
## [1] "female" "male"
# Pre-filtering
keep <- rowSums(counts(dds) >= 10) >= min(summary(dds$barcode))

sum(keep)
## [1] 11773
dds <- dds[keep, ]

# Relevel male as reference to analyze as Female vs. Male
dds$gender <- relevel(dds$gender, ref = "male")


# Perform DE Analysis
dds <- DESeq(dds)

# Create contrasts matrix
contr.matrix <- makeContrasts(female, male, levels = colnames(design))
contr.matrix
##         Contrasts
## Levels   female male
##   female      1    0
##   male        0    1
# Removing heteroskedasticity from the count data
v <- voom(x, design, plot = FALSE)

# Fitting linear models for comparisons of interest
vfit <- lmFit(v, design)

vfit <- contrasts.fit(vfit, contrasts=contr.matrix)

efit <- eBayes(vfit)

res_limma <- topTable(efit, coef=1, number=Inf, adjust.method="BH")

Find the number of genes that were found significantly upregulated by both limma and DESeq2

# DESeq2 significantly upregulated genes
res_DESeq_up <- filter(as.data.frame(res), res$log2FoldChange>0)

# limma significantly upregulated genes
res_limma_up <-  filter(as.data.frame(res_limma), res_limma$logFC > 0)

# Adding as a rownames
rownames(res_limma_up) <- res_limma_up$ID

#Removing ID column
res_limma_up <- res_limma_up[,2:6]

#To find the number of genes both limma and DESeq2
sum(rownames(res_DESeq_up) %in% rownames(res_limma_up))

# Removing heteroskedasticity from the count data
v <- voom(x, design, plot = FALSE)

# Fitting linear models for comparisons of interest
vfit <- lmFit(v, design)

vfit <- contrasts.fit(vfit, contrasts=contr.matrix)

efit <- eBayes(vfit)

tfit <- treat(vfit, lfc=1) # 2 fold up/downregulation threshold

res_limma_CD8A <- topTable(efit, coef=1, number=Inf, adjust.method="BH")
